1
00:00:01,520 --> 00:00:05,830
Here is what most of market gurus are teaching
you about moving averages.

2
00:00:05,830 --> 00:00:10,360
You take a short-term moving average and a
long-term moving average and you buy and sell

3
00:00:10,360 --> 00:00:12,049
when you see crossovers.

4
00:00:12,049 --> 00:00:19,460
Nice, so you buy here, the price rallies,
you exit here with 100% profit, you sell here,

5
00:00:19,460 --> 00:00:25,539
another winning trade, one more buy, another
win...this is too easy, like printing money.

6
00:00:25,539 --> 00:00:32,480
What they don’t tell you is that these results
happen maybe 10%-15% of trading days, if you’re

7
00:00:32,480 --> 00:00:33,540
lucky.

8
00:00:33,540 --> 00:00:36,620
Here is how the normal trading day looks like.

9
00:00:36,620 --> 00:00:40,650
Not so profitable anymore, right, with all
the choppiness and false signals?

10
00:00:40,650 --> 00:00:45,550
If you follow a crossover pattern, in 2 weeks
your account is gone, guaranteed.

11
00:00:45,550 --> 00:00:51,190
If i learned something in my over 10 years’
experience of trading is that moving average

12
00:00:51,190 --> 00:00:53,660
crossovers don’t work like advertised.

13
00:00:53,660 --> 00:00:58,649
So in the following minutes, we’ll talk
about moving averages, how you should use

14
00:00:58,649 --> 00:01:04,300
them correctly and I’ll show you how i use
the crossovers in my trading plan.

15
00:01:04,300 --> 00:01:09,139
Before we continue, if you’re new to our
channel, make sure you subscribe, click the

16
00:01:09,139 --> 00:01:13,579
notifications bell and leave a like to show
your support.

17
00:01:13,579 --> 00:01:18,420
Now, why are moving average crossovers so
popular?

18
00:01:18,420 --> 00:01:24,219
Because, a moving average is a trend indicator,
and you were told that the trend is your friend,

19
00:01:24,219 --> 00:01:28,209
so why not using 2 or 3 moving averages, to
increase your chances.

20
00:01:28,209 --> 00:01:33,450
Here is a hard truth and, please keep in mind
that this is simply my discovery after 10

21
00:01:33,450 --> 00:01:35,119
years of trading.

22
00:01:35,119 --> 00:01:38,640
Moving averages crossovers don’t work on
lower time frames.

23
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:39,640
Period.

24
00:01:39,640 --> 00:01:42,130
I’ve tested hundreds, thousands of combinations.

25
00:01:42,130 --> 00:01:46,159
Some of them were decent, some of them damaged
my account.

26
00:01:46,159 --> 00:01:53,920
You’ll have a hard time trading crossovers
on the 5-minute or 15-minutes charts.

27
00:01:53,920 --> 00:01:58,630
If you found a magic crossover that works
on lower timeframes, go ahead and share it

28
00:01:58,630 --> 00:02:03,899
with me, because i simply wasn’t able to
record consistent profit by trading crossovers

29
00:02:03,899 --> 00:02:05,770
on lower time frames.

30
00:02:05,770 --> 00:02:10,750
On higher time frames, well, we have another
story here, and you might be able to profit

31
00:02:10,750 --> 00:02:12,250
from crossovers.

32
00:02:12,250 --> 00:02:17,810
But first, let me explain why is dangerous
for you to trade crossovers on lower time

33
00:02:17,810 --> 00:02:24,080
frames and why this strategy will most likely
lead to frustrations and bad results.

34
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:30,010
The biggest drawbacks of moving averages is
the fact they lag price.

35
00:02:30,010 --> 00:02:34,140
Price moves first and the moving average moves
second.

36
00:02:34,140 --> 00:02:36,630
You are always behind the price.

37
00:02:36,630 --> 00:02:38,720
The moving average is a trend following indicator.

38
00:02:38,720 --> 00:02:42,620
It can only tell you when the trend has already
happened.

39
00:02:42,620 --> 00:02:46,430
You can’t forecast a new trend with a moving
average because it’s a lagging indicator.

40
00:02:46,430 --> 00:02:52,540
Pay attention in this chart that the moving
average was still rising whilst price hit

41
00:02:52,540 --> 00:02:58,530
the resistance level and went down by a considerable
amount.

42
00:02:58,530 --> 00:03:01,760
The second problem with moving averages is
the noise.

43
00:03:01,760 --> 00:03:06,180
One of the best things about using moving
averages for trading is that they are designed

44
00:03:06,180 --> 00:03:11,960
to smooth out the erratic price data so that
you can be able to detect and stay with the

45
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:12,960
trend.

46
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:17,310
However, even the best moving averages suffer
from noise.

47
00:03:17,310 --> 00:03:22,900
On lower time frames, you will witness many
false signals if the market is consolidating

48
00:03:22,900 --> 00:03:29,550
or the price spikes up and down due to higher
volatility.

49
00:03:29,550 --> 00:03:33,840
Another drawback of a moving average crossover
system is the sideways markets.

50
00:03:33,840 --> 00:03:39,620
Nothing is more frustrating than trying to
use a crossover strategy in a sideways market!

51
00:03:39,620 --> 00:03:42,150
Your stop losses won’t stand a chance!

52
00:03:42,150 --> 00:03:47,920
Regardless of what type of moving average
you use in a sideways market, they will not

53
00:03:47,920 --> 00:03:48,920
work effectively.

54
00:03:48,920 --> 00:03:54,240
So, if you are a day trader, I would say is
better to avoid crossover strategies on lower

55
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:55,710
time frames.

56
00:03:55,710 --> 00:03:59,900
There are better ways to use a moving average.

57
00:03:59,900 --> 00:04:04,470
Moving averages are great to determine the
trend direction of your instrument.

58
00:04:04,470 --> 00:04:09,700
While price action and structure should be
your main focus, you can get a general idea

59
00:04:09,700 --> 00:04:12,510
of the market direction with a moving average.

60
00:04:12,510 --> 00:04:16,049
So, here is how you could take advantage of
a moving average:

61
00:04:16,049 --> 00:04:24,389
First, to identify and confirm market trend
While keeping in mind that are lagging indicators,

62
00:04:24,389 --> 00:04:31,580
you can use the slope of the moving average:
up sloping is an uptrend and down sloping

63
00:04:31,580 --> 00:04:33,729
is downtrend.

64
00:04:33,729 --> 00:04:41,729
You can also use price location: if price
above moving average, look for long trades.

65
00:04:41,729 --> 00:04:46,060
Below the average you would look for short
opportunities.

66
00:04:46,060 --> 00:04:51,439
A stock is considered to be in an uptrend
when the price is above a moving average and

67
00:04:51,439 --> 00:04:57,689
the ma’s slope is upward
A stock is considered to be in a downtrend

68
00:04:57,689 --> 00:05:04,550
when the price is below a moving average and
the ma’s slope is downward

69
00:05:04,550 --> 00:05:09,740
The second way you could use a moving average
is as support and resistance level.

70
00:05:09,740 --> 00:05:15,710
Moving averages offer traders dynamic areas
of support and resistance because are changing

71
00:05:15,710 --> 00:05:18,120
depending on recent price action.

72
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:24,180
Being so common and followed by so many traders,
you can often see on charts that the popular

73
00:05:24,180 --> 00:05:28,330
moving averages work excellent as support
and resistance levels.

74
00:05:28,330 --> 00:05:35,529
A simple ma could be considered as a dynamic
area of support or resistance

75
00:05:35,529 --> 00:05:40,529
The area between two moving averages could
also be considered as a dynamic area of support

76
00:05:40,529 --> 00:05:42,319
or resistance.

77
00:05:42,319 --> 00:05:50,210
A longer-term moving average like ma 200 has
a greater relevance to the price, and offers

78
00:05:50,210 --> 00:05:54,759
less false signals, compared to shorter-term
moving averages.

79
00:05:54,759 --> 00:05:58,370
Now, let’s come back to the crossovers.

80
00:05:58,370 --> 00:06:04,259
So a moving average crossover system will
catch good movements when markets are trending.

81
00:06:04,259 --> 00:06:10,150
However, when markets are trading in a range,
this system is subject to many losing trades.

82
00:06:10,150 --> 00:06:13,860
And on lower timeframes, the odds are not
in your favor.

83
00:06:13,860 --> 00:06:16,660
So, are moving average crossovers useless?

84
00:06:16,660 --> 00:06:18,870
Well, not quite.

85
00:06:18,870 --> 00:06:24,740
On higher timeframes, for traders and investors
that hold positions for several months using

86
00:06:24,740 --> 00:06:29,990
higher time frames like daily, weekly, or
even monthly charts, the moving averages have

87
00:06:29,990 --> 00:06:34,999
higher chances of indicating a valid signal.

88
00:06:34,999 --> 00:06:36,639
But there’s another problem here.

89
00:06:36,639 --> 00:06:42,430
A two-moving average crossover system is usually
a “stop and-reverse” strategy, meaning

90
00:06:42,430 --> 00:06:47,900
that you will be in the market at all times
when used as a mechanical strategy.

91
00:06:47,900 --> 00:06:53,310
Once an entry is triggered, you will remain
in the market until the opposite signal is

92
00:06:53,310 --> 00:06:59,520
generated, at which time your current position
will be liquidated and a new one entered in

93
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:01,560
the direction of the new signal.

94
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:05,440
But even on higher time frames, this strategy
is risky.

95
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:13,300
So, i would only take long positions and completely
ignore short signals.

96
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:18,039
And here’s another important tip which will
cut your losses even more.

97
00:07:18,039 --> 00:07:23,939
When a buy signal is generated, you must wait
for the bar to be completely finished before

98
00:07:23,939 --> 00:07:25,610
entering the trade.

99
00:07:25,610 --> 00:07:31,369
I can’t remember how many times I traded
a crossover signal without waiting for the

100
00:07:31,369 --> 00:07:32,979
candle to be closed.

101
00:07:32,979 --> 00:07:38,419
So, wait for the candle to close and confirm
the crossover, it will save you a lot of bad

102
00:07:38,419 --> 00:07:41,370
entries.

103
00:07:41,370 --> 00:07:46,810
Once you have triggered your entry, there
are several ways to manage this trade.

104
00:07:46,810 --> 00:07:52,139
Traditionally, you would remain in the trade
until an opposite signal appears.

105
00:07:52,139 --> 00:07:57,319
While waiting for an opposite signal to exit
your position may be the “normal” approach,

106
00:07:57,319 --> 00:08:02,419
you may find this method to be inconsistent,
depending on the market’s behavior.

107
00:08:02,419 --> 00:08:08,300
This approach will often lead to extremely
late exits, which can severely cut into your

108
00:08:08,300 --> 00:08:09,330
profits.

109
00:08:09,330 --> 00:08:15,810
Instead, you could try other tactics like
using a traditional trailing stop, using a

110
00:08:15,810 --> 00:08:24,520
single moving average crossover exit, using
a fixed profit target, using Fibonacci extensions

111
00:08:24,520 --> 00:08:31,259
as targets or using visual support and resistance
levels as targets.

112
00:08:31,259 --> 00:08:41,250
I personally use the 200 EMA and the 20 EMA
on the daily chart to search for buy entries

113
00:08:41,250 --> 00:08:47,820
on stocks with good fundamentals, but these
2 moving averages are not set in stone.

114
00:08:47,820 --> 00:08:52,940
Depending on the stock traded, you can have
other values for your crossover signals in

115
00:08:52,940 --> 00:08:54,760
a daily timeframe.

116
00:08:54,760 --> 00:08:57,300
As you may know, the market will change over
time.

117
00:08:57,300 --> 00:09:04,380
At times, a market may be quiet and trending,
while other times it may be erratic and directionless,

118
00:09:04,380 --> 00:09:10,170
so you should adjust the moving averages of
your crossover system to find the best fit.

119
00:09:10,170 --> 00:09:17,190
So, no shortcuts here, there is no universal
moving average crossover that works on any

120
00:09:17,190 --> 00:09:18,190
market.

121
00:09:18,190 --> 00:09:25,090
You must continually back test and adjust
your moving averages by yourself.

122
00:09:25,090 --> 00:09:29,410
With today’s trading platforms, you can
even scan the entire market of stocks with

123
00:09:29,410 --> 00:09:33,510
specific criteria to find those that are behaving
in a similar manner.

124
00:09:33,510 --> 00:09:39,000
You only need a good stock screener, and trade
stocks with good fundamentals.

125
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:43,350
To increase your chances when trading a crossover
strategy, it’s good to have fundamentals

126
00:09:43,350 --> 00:09:49,010
on your side, this is why i only trade companies
what have good perspectives.

127
00:09:49,010 --> 00:09:53,650
With a stock screener, you still have to do
your homework, but you can set screens to

128
00:09:53,650 --> 00:09:58,330
create your watch list based on your crossover
conditions and it’s going to save you a

129
00:09:58,330 --> 00:10:02,760
lot of time, especially if you’re monitoring
hundreds or thousands of stocks.

130
00:10:02,760 --> 00:10:08,640
So, don’t neglect the power of a stock screener,
it can help you a lot in your trading.

131
00:10:08,640 --> 00:10:13,511
Now, if you found value and learned something
new, make sure you subscribe to our channel,

132
00:10:13,511 --> 00:10:18,460
turn on the notifications so you don’t miss
future uploads and leave us a like to show

133
00:10:18,460 --> 00:10:20,260
your support.

134
00:10:20,260 --> 00:10:20,690
Until next time.

